init_text:
Are We Being Bad Citizens If We Don't Keep Up With the News?

In your opinion, are we being bad citizens if we don't keep up with the news? Do you think all people have some responsibility to know what is going on in the world? Does engaging with current events actually do anything at all? Why do you think the way you do?

---

In my opinion,

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I think it is okay to take a break of news sometimes.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: violence and terrorism around the world and just want to tune out and not dwell on it.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The same goes with social media.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: All throughout social media you see stuff about the news, and people will not hesitate to share it with their followers.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Do I believe there is a responsibility to know what is going on in the world?

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I feel you should save your energy from worrying, and use it to purify your soul and become a better person.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Maybe they don't realize that tuning out some news would greatly help them escape from some of their worries and lessen stress on their lives.
